                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/1374: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-22T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >January 22, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 22—7:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. The Soviet Embassy has confirmed reports that an agreement for the sale of
                    the Chinese Eastern Railway was reached last night and has stated that the press
                    reports of the terms thereof are substantially correct. The agreement is subject
                    to confirmation by the governments concerned and certain minor details remain to
                    be adjusted. It appears, however, that the sale will now [be] definitely
                    consummated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
